title: Direct Talk
subTitle: Renowned watchmaker Daizo Makihara discusses his works and passion for creating analogue watches in the digital world.

title: IMPACTS:Climates Change the World
subTitle: Water levels all over the world are rising, with regions at low elevation in particular danger. Vietnam's rice fields have been subjected to floods, endangering production of precious food supplies.

title: NHK World Japan
subTitle: On those hot, humid summer nights, nothing can get in the way of sleep like mosquitoes on the hunt. We learn about the tools the Edo townspeople had at their disposal to fight the pesky insects.

title: Medical Frontiers
subTitle: A large-scale study in Japan has shown that improving one's diet and lifestyle can slow the progression of chronic kidney disease. Clinical trials in regenerative medicine are also underway.

title: Gunma-chan
subTitle: Join Gunmachan and friends for playful adventures full of laughter and curiosity, and explore the charm of Gunma Prefecture's traditions, culture, and specialties.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: MATSURI: The Heartbeat of Japan
subTitle: At Hibuse Matsuri, the Fire Prevention Festival, men douse buildings in water as a prayer for protection from fire. At this event held in January, bonfires and sake help to keep people warm.

title: Nun's Seasonal Calendar
subTitle: On the winter date of Shokan, the nuns pick herbs in the temple's garden and make seasonal rice porridge. Later, they prepare kan-koji fermented rice and pickled napa cabbage on Daikan.

title: Design X Stories
subTitle: Today's theme: Design Hunting in Tottori. On the Sea of Japan coast, the Tottori Sand Dunes create unique, everchanging views. Our design hunt explores a culture with deep roots in the natural world.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Cinematic Journey
subTitle: Kyle Card hikes along the 621 miles trail following the Pacific Coast in northern Japan, where he discovers local lifestyles, stunning nature, traces of the area's 2011 disaster, and resilient people.

title: Ramen Japan
subTitle: Tokushima ramen means tonkotsu, and this one-of-a-kind bowl of ramen from Tokushima Prefecture is topped with pork belly and raw egg.

title: Asia Insight
subTitle: Cases of Online Sexual Abuse and Exploitation of Children (OSAEC) are on the rise. A visit to a Filipino NGO that protects victims of online sexual abuse, and helps them to recover.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Biz Stream Special Edition
subTitle: NHK WORLD-JAPAN presents a wide range of programs from news, current affairs, documentaries, etc. focusing on Japan and Asia.

title: One in Every Japanese
subTitle: One in 36 people in Japan are foreign residents. As its population declines, looking at Japanese society in a new era of foreign workers, through an IT startup where 90% of staff are foreigners.

title: Ama Divers Restoring The Earthquake-Hit Seabed
subTitle: The filmmaker sheds light on Wajima's ama divers surveying the seabed and striving to revive their tradition after 2024's devastating natural disasters.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Chatroom Japan
subTitle: Marvin finds himself becoming a data analyst after being turned down by 50 companies during his job search.

title: Japan's Top Inventions
subTitle: Taking a closer look at eggshell field chalk.

title: Japanology Plus
subTitle: A feudal lord admired by John F. Kennedy, Uesugi Yozan prioritized the well-being of his people. This time, in part two, we look at how his policies guided his domain along the path to sustainability.

subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

subTitle: The Hiroshima and Nagasaki Peace Messengers visit the United Nations in Geneva each year. We join them as they call for nuclear abolition and see the complexities of global politics in a new light.
